node.text:
Though my progress has been slow, it has been steady and consistent. I have gone from sleeping in my car, on trains to living at the mercy of other’s benevolence, to sleeping in a futon in my friends living room, living in a small box where I could afford rent and save my money, to living in a beautiful loft that was everything I once hoped I would one day experience, to finally building my dream home from the ground up. 

Psalm 126: 1-5 simply says
1 When the Lord turned again the captivity of Zion, we were like them that dream.
2 Then was our mouth filled with laughter, and our tongue with singing: then said they among the heathen, The Lord hath done great things for them.
3 The Lord hath done great things for us; whereof we are glad. 
4 Turn again our captivity, O Lord, as the streams in the south. 
5 They that sow in tears shall reap in joy.
 
The promise in verse 5 gets me every single time. “They that sow in tears shall reap in joy.” 
It has been a journey, BUT GOD!!!! Nothing is too big or small for God. 
Simply ask, conceive the image of the life you desire subconsciously, prepare by doing the work, pray, obey and continue to give thanks for all God has done and it will come to pass. It is God’s desire to advance us and take us to new dimensions in this life. Please take advantage of that relationship, for without an understanding of who God is we are simply nothing.

THANK YOU LORD!!! 
Father I stand today as a point of contact for those who are hoping for you to visit them, may they experience the splendor of my God. May their lips also testify of  my Jehovah Jireh. For you are nothing but good and holy and perfect in all your ways. May you make your ways known to us that we may continue to follow you always. May our lips from this day only utter praises to you Jehovah Nissi. May this season be a season full of testimonies for everyone who believes. THANK YOU LORD, for nothing is impossible for you.

node.text:
with loved ones and in spaces that fuel our excitement. I recently started taking a class with @masterclass on interior decor to make my home aesthetically enticing for the holidays. 

I personally love Kelly Wearstler’s approach to design. As a fellow creative, I enjoy studying other people’s creative process. Kelly’s approach to design is all interconnected from her experiences.

Excited to learn and apply all that I have learned from this course in my space. Taking this course has sparked my excitement for design, and I look forward to creating a space that fosters the joy of the season for my loved ones. There are endless options of courses to take on MasterClass and I look forward to diving into classes from Bobbi Brown, Annie Leibovitz and more. There’s a special holiday offer for the upcoming season. Give one annual  membership and get one free! Treat yourself and a friend a course of your choice. #TodaysTheDay

node.title: The holidays are full of shared moments in comfort

node.text:
One constant thing about our skin is that it is ever changing. Whether due to a switch hormonal levels,  travelling, change in climate, stress, sleep or the lack of thereof, our skin adjusts to external factors.

Learning about my skin type at an early age has allowed for me to understand exactly what my skin requires. I was able to identify common misconceptions, including the flawed idea that people like me do not need to moisturise! Our sebaceous glands overwork themselves when we deprive our skin of the right amount of nourishment, which leads to a change in texture and a lacklustre appearance of the skin.

That’s why I love using Augustinus Bader’s products, which all contain the patented TFC8 formula backed by 30 years of science, delivering key nutrients directly to the skin cells. I use The Cleansing Balm to purify and nourish, The Essence, Exfoliating Toner with TFC8 to exfoliate, tone and renew cells and The Face Oil for a hydrated, radiant glow.

It is essential to learn more about our skin so we can give it the right amount of nourishment— internally and topically, as the protective organ that it is – and use products in our regimen that offer antioxidant and environmental protection, like @augustinusbader. 

#FindYourFormula #Ad

It’s everywhere around us if we pause long enough to see it. To feel it. To capture it.

node.text:
We’ve all been static, not able to explore the spaces that we’ve desired and as the times have changed, we’ve been forced to appreciate the simple things, and the beauty in that simplicity.
The LUMIX G100 provides the ability to create moments in time, to steal those moments with a snapshot and mark those for posterity, for generations to come. And as explicitly designed for content creators, the LUMIX G100 is small, agile and responsive to face detection, providing the freedom to capture and freeze those lasting moments through its lenses.
#LUMIXVloglife #LUMIXG100 #ShotOnLUMIX

node.text: Confidence is a journey. We do not just arrive at being overly confident in who we are. It is through trial and error, mistakes and failures, that we arrive at the point where we embrace the skin we are in. In part of my self-care journey, I have leaned more towards a foundation that provides the benefits of intense hydration; and with the lightweight and glowing coverage given from the @ArmaniBeauty Neo Nude Foundation I own my essence of self-confidence. #ArmaniNeoNude #Ad

node.text:
The  Eela Collection 

Eela is a term that originates from the Abua language, spoken by a small minority of people in Southern Nigeria. It means ‘wealth’ in the complete sense of the word. The pieces in this collection are an embodiment of this said word, of the beauty and sense of internal wealth that is translated to the outside with each wear. While wealth in itself may have varied interpretations, it is essentially the a sense or reality of abundance. Each handcrafted piece in this collection is aimed at arming the wearer with an abundance of confidence and awareness of self worth, as if to say - I have arrived. 

Here’s a toast to living in Abundance. Cc @vanessa_gyimah x @apueela.m  #itsscelebrationbetches Produced by: @aucostudio 🎥: @paolamutis

node.text: #AD Took my girls out for an intimate picnic in our Spanish villa courtesy of @TanquerayUSA! Big thank you to them for making our time together remarkable with their perfectly blended craft cocktails in a can, each made with real Tanqueray Gin and original brand recipes. Grateful for the opportunity to create beautiful experiences for the ones I love.

node.text: Took some time to prioritize the health of my mind with @clubmed at their stunning eco-chic property @clubmedmichesplayaesmeralda. It was the perfect getaway that I had been longing for. My time at Miches was exactly what my mind, body and soul needed. The vibrant hues of the Caribbean, chic swim-up bar and wellness palapa, were perfect for mindful moments. The resort lives up to its nickname as the hidden gem of the Dominican Republic. #clubmed #ClubMedMiches #sponsored

node.text:
My heart is still overflowing with joy, and gratitude from this weekend’s festivities!!!! 

Understanding that this is not the end but celebrating the present. This milestone in particular is greater than myself. It is an achievement that has put smiles on the faces of those who could see the trajectory of where my life was headed when my reality looked like I was going nowhere.
 
What’s amazing about most of the people who have been a part of my journey over the past 7yrs is that they recognized my value irrespective of where I found myself back then and still treated me like Gold.

It is because they believed and pushed me that I can celebrate today. Jim Rohn says, “surround yourself with those who you can go through the seasons of life with”. 

To my family and my chosen family, thank you for always being the pillar that holds me together. I love you all. 🤎

🎈: @boomsycrafts
🎥: @lloyd_mack
